DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Diagnostic Imaging Lymphoscintigraphy Performed Yes No Indicator

Lymphoscintigraphy is used to find the sentinel lymph node (the first node to receive lymph from a tumor), which may be removed and checked for tumor cells. Lymphoscintigraphy is also used to diagnose certain diseases or conditions, such as lymphoma or lymphedema.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Adjuvant Therapy Paclitaxel Albumin-Stabilized Nanoparticle Formulation Administered Yes No Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no indicator of information related to the administration of nab-paclitaxel in anoadjuvant setting.  Nab-paclitaxel is a Cremophor EL-free, albumin-stabilized nanoparticle formulation of the natural taxane paclitaxel with antineoplastic activity. Paclitaxel binds to and stabilizes microtubules, preventing their depolymerization and so inhibiting cellular motility, mitosis, and replication. This formulation solubilizes paclitaxel without the use of the solvent Cremophor, thereby permitting the administration of larger doses of paclitaxel while avoiding the toxic effects associated with Cremophor.treatment plan.
DataElementQueryResults.origin: NCCTG CRF:North Central Cancer Treatment Group Case Report Form
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: Changed from CTEP to Alliance for by script Fri Oct 25 15:25:44 EDT 2013

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Adjuvant Therapy Doxorubicin Administered Yes No Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no indicator of information related to the administration of doxorubicin in an adjuvant setting.  Doxorubicin is an anthracycline antineoplastic antibiotic isolated from the fungus Streptococcus peucetius var. caesius.  Doxorubicin intercalates into DNA and interacts with topoisomerase II, thereby inhibiting DNA replication and repair and RNA and protein synthesis.  This agent also produces toxic free-radical intermediates and interacts with cell membrane lipids causing lipid peroxidation.
DataElementQueryResults.origin: NCCTG CRF:North Central Cancer Treatment Group Case Report Form
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: Changed from CTEP to Alliance for by script Fri Oct 25 15:25:44 EDT 2013

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Adjuvant Therapy Epirubicin Administered Yes No Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no indicator of information related to the administration of epirubicin in an adjuvant setting.  Epirubicin is a 4'-epi-isomer of the anthracycline antineoplastic antibiotic doxorubicin.  Epirubicin intercalates into DNA and inhibits topoisomerase II, thereby inhibiting DNA replication and ultimately, interfering with RNA and protein synthesis.  This agent also produces toxic free-radical intermediates and interacts with cell membrane lipids causing lipid peroxidation.
DataElementQueryResults.origin: NCCTG CRF:North Central Cancer Treatment Group Case Report Form
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: Changed from CTEP to Alliance for by script Fri Oct 25 15:25:44 EDT 2013

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Adjuvant Therapy Idarubicin Administered Yes No Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no indicator of information related to the administration of idarubicin in an adjuvant setting.  Idarubicin is a semisynthetic anthracycline antineoplastic antibiotic derived from daunorubicin.  Idarubicin intercalates into DNA and interacts with topoisomerase II, thereby inhibiting DNA replication and repair and RNA and protein synthesis.  Due to its high lipophilicity, idarubicin penetrates cell membranes better than other anthracycline antibiotics.
DataElementQueryResults.origin: NCCTG CRF:North Central Cancer Treatment Group Case Report Form
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: Changed from CTEP to Alliance for by script Fri Oct 25 15:25:44 EDT 2013

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Adjuvant Therapy Cyclophosphamide Administered Yes No Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no indicator of information related to the administration of cyclophosphamide in an adjuvant setting.  Cyclophosphamide is a synthetic alkylating agent chemically related to the nitrogen mustards with antineoplastic and immunosuppressive activities.  In the liver, cyclophosphamide is converted to the active metabolites aldophosphamide and phosphoramide mustard, which bind to DNA, thereby inhibiting DNA replication and initiating cell death.
DataElementQueryResults.origin: NCCTG CRF:North Central Cancer Treatment Group Case Report Form
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: Changed from CTEP to Alliance for by script Fri Oct 25 15:25:44 EDT 2013

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Adjuvant Therapy Methotrexate Administered Yes No Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no indicator of information related to the administration of methotrexate in an adjuvant setting.  Methotrexate is an antimetabolite with antineoplastic and immunomodulating properties.  Methotrxate inhibits the enzyme dihydrofolate reductase, resulting in inhibition of purine nucleotide and thymidylate synthesis and, subsequently, inhibition of DNA and RNA syntheses.  Methotrexate also exhibits potent immunosuppressant properties.
DataElementQueryResults.origin: NCCTG CRF:North Central Cancer Treatment Group Case Report Form
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: Changed from CTEP to Alliance for by script Fri Oct 25 15:25:44 EDT 2013

DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no indicator for information related to the observation of a systemic, serious, and life-threatening disorder characterized by erythematous and necrotic lesions in the skin and mucous membranes that are associated with bullous detachment of the epidermis. DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Medication Aspirin Administered Use Category
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The category used to classify the frequency and duration of use related to the administration of aspirin, an orally administered non-steroidal anti-inflammatory agent. Acetylsalicylic acid binds to and acetylates serine residues in cyclo-oxygenases, resulting in decreased synthesis of prostaglandin, platelet aggregation, and inflammation. This agent exhibits analgesic, antipyretic, and anticoagulant properties.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Medication Acetaminophen Administered Use Category
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The category used to classify the frequency and duration of use related to the administration of acetaminophen, a drug that reduces pain and fever (but not inflammation).  It belongs to the family of drugs called analgesics.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Medication Metformin Administered Medication Use Category
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The category used to classify the frequency and duration of use related to the administration of metformin, a biguanide with antihyperglycemic activity. Metformin exerts its action by improving hepatic sensitivity to insulin, thereby suppressing hepatic glucose production and increasing hepatic glycogen stores. In addition, metformin increases the number and/or affinity of insulin receptors on cell surface membranes in muscle and adipose tissue, thereby increasing the sensitivity to insulin at receptor and post-receptor binding sites and increasing glucose uptake peripherally.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Therapy HMG-CoA Reductase Inhibitor Administered Use Category

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Person Diesel Exhaust Particulate Exposure Yes No Unknown Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no/unknown indicator for information related to a person being exposed to a complex mixture of combustion products of diesel fuel including carbon monoxide, carbon dioxide, sulfur oxides, nitrogen oxides, volatile hydrocarbons, aldehydes, alkenes, alkanes and nitroarenes, polycyclic aromatic hydrocarbons and other derivates.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Person Respirable Crystalline Silica Exposure Yes No Unknown Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no/unknown indicator for information related to a person being exposed to a widespread, naturally occurring, crystalline metal oxide that consists of different forms including quartz, cristobalite, tridymite, tripoli, ganister, chert and novaculite. Respirable crystalline silica is found in industry in metal and nonmetal mining and milling operations as well as in foundries, ceramic industries and at construction sites. Inhalation exposure to respirable crystalline silica causes chronic silicosis, emphysema, lymph node fibrosis and is associated with an increased risk of developing lung cancer.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Person Wood Dust Exposure Yes No Unknown Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no/unknown indicator for information related to a person being exposed to a light- to dark-colored granular solid mixture that is generated when timber is processed, such as when it is chipped, sawed, turned, drilled or sanded. The chemical composition of wood dust depends on the species of tree and consists mainly of cellulose, polyoses and lignin, with a large and variable number of substances with lower relative molecular mass. Wood dust is not typically produced for specific uses. However, it is used commercially for wood composts. The primary routes of potential human exposure to wood dust are inhalation and dermal contact. It is known to be a human carcinogen.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Person Mineral Dust Exposure Yes No Unknown Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no/unknown indicator for information related to a person being exposed to dust from a mineral (a solid, homogeneous, inorganic substance occurring in nature and having a definite chemical composition solid, homogeneous, inorganic substance occurring in nature and having a definite chemical composition).

This is also known as the Halabi nomogram.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Prior Therapy Cisplatin Administered Yes No Unknown Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no/unknown indicator related to the prior administration of cisplatin, an alkylating-like inorganic platinum agent (cis-diamminedichloroplatinum) with antineoplastic activity. Cisplatin forms highly reactive, charged, platinum complexes which bind to nucleophilic groups such as GC-rich sites in DNA inducing intrastrand and interstrand DNA cross-links, as well as DNA-protein cross-links. These cross-links result in apoptosis and cell growth inhibition.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Prior Therapy Carboplatin Administered Yes No Unknown Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no/unknown indicator related to the prior administration of carboplatin, a second-generation platinum compound with a broad spectrum of antineoplastic properties.  Carboplatin contains a platinum atom complexed with two ammonia groups and a cyclobutane-dicarboxyl residue.  This agent is activated intracellularly to form reactive platinum complexes that bind to nucleophilic groups such as GC-rich sites in DNA, thereby inducing intrastrand and interstrand DNA cross-links, as well as DNA-protein cross-links.  These carboplatin-induced DNA and protein effects result in apoptosis and cell growth inhibition.  This agent possesses tumoricidal activity similar to that of its parent compound, cisplatin, but is more stable and less toxic.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Prior Therapy Vinorelbine Administered Yes No Unknown Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no/unknown indicator related to the prior administration of vinorelbine, a semisynthetic vinca alkaloid. Vinorelbine binds to tubulin and prevents formation of the mitotic spindle, resulting in the arrest of tumor cell growth in metaphase. This agent may also interfere with amino acid, cyclic AMP. and glutathione metabolism; calmodulin-dependent Ca++ -transport ATPase activity; cellular respiration; and nucleic acid and lipid biosynthesis.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Prior Therapy Paclitaxel Administered Yes No Unknown Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no/unknown indicator related to the prior administration of paclitaxel, a compound extracted from the Pacific yew tree Taxus brevifolia with antineoplastic activity.  Paclitaxel binds to tubulin and inhibits the disassembly of microtubules, thereby resulting in the inhibition of cell division.  This agent also induces apoptosis by binding to and blocking the function of the apoptosis inhibitor protein Bcl-2 (B-cell Leukemia 2).

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Prior Therapy Gemcitabine Administered Yes No Unknown Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no/unknown indicator related to the prior administration of gemcitabine, a broad-spectrum antimetabolite and deoxycytidine analogue with antineoplastic activity. Upon administration, gemcitabine is converted into the active metabolites difluorodeoxycytidine diphosphate (dFdCDP) and difluorodeoxycytidine triphosphate (dFdCTP) by deoxycytidine kinase. dFdCTP competes with deoxycytidine triphosphate (dCTP) and is incorporated into DNA.  This locks DNA polymerase thereby resulting in "masked termination" during DNA replication. On the other hand, dFdCDP inhibits ribonucleotide reductase, thereby decreasing the deoxynucleotide pool available for DNA synthesis. The reduction in the intracellular concentration of dCTP potentiates the incorporation of dFdCTP into DNA.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Prior Therapy Docetaxel Administered Yes No Unknown Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no/unknown indicator related to the prior administration of docetaxel, a semi-synthetic, second-generation taxane derived from a compound found in the European yew tree, Taxus baccata.  Docetaxel displays potent and broad antineoplastic properties; it binds to and stabilizes tubulin, thereby inhibiting microtubule disassembly which results in cell- cycle arrest at the G2/M phase and cell death.  This agent also inhibits pro-angiogenic factors such as vascular endothelial growth factor (VEGF) and displays immunomodulatory and pro-inflammatory properties by inducing various mediators of the inflammatory response.  Docetaxel has been studied for use as a radiation-sensitizing agent.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Prior Therapy Pemetrexed Administered Yes No Unknown Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no/unknown indicator related to the prior administration of pemetrexed, a synthetic pyrimidine-based antifolate. Pemetrexed binds to and inhibits the enzyme thymidylate synthase (TS), which catalyses the methylation of 2'-deoxyuridine-5'-monophosphate (dUMP) to 2'-deoxythymidine-5'-monophosphate (dTMP), an essential precursor in DNA synthesis.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Person MGMT Abnormality Verification Clinical Trial Eligibility Criteria Yes No Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no indicator related to the verification of a MGMT abnormality.  MGMT is an enzyme that transfers methyl groups from O(6) methylguanine and other methylated moities of DNA, to a cysteine residue in itself, thus repairing alkylated DNA in a single step reaction.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: FACT-E Questionnaire Complete Yes No Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no indicator for information related to completion of the subscale questionnaire complement to the FACT-G developed specifically for evaluating quality of life of esophageal cancer patients.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: FACT-Hep Questionnaire Assessment Yes No Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no indicator for information related to the assessment of a subscale complement to the FACT-G questionnaire developed specifically for evaluating quality of life of patients with hepatobiliary cancer (liver, bile duct and pancreas).

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Caregiver Quality of Life Absent Assessment Reason
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The reason a Quality of Life assessment for a protocol was not completed by the Caregiver.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Chart Abstraction Complete Yes No Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no indicator for information related to the completion of the process of reading the record of a health encounter to determine and document the condition the patient had, the cause, and the treatment prescribed.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Chart Abstraction Complete Date
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The date related to the completion of the process of reading the record of a health encounter to determine and document the condition the patient had, the cause, and the treatment prescribed.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Patient Social Work Referral Yes No Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no indicator for information related to a patient referral to social work, which is the use of community resources, individual case work, or group work to promote the adaptive capacities of individuals in relation to their social and economic environments.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Patient Psychologist Referral Yes No Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no indicator for information related to a patient referral to a psychologist, a specialist who can talk with patients and their families about emotional and personal matters, and can help them make decisions.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Patient Pastoral Counselor Referral Yes No Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no indicator for information related to a patient referral to pastoral care, a specialist who can talk with patients and their families about emotional and personal matters, and can help them make decisions. A person trained in both psychology and theology who can provide psychological and spiritual guidance to individuals and families.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Patient Palliative Therapy Personnel Assessment Yes No Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no indicator for information related to a patient's assessment by palliative care personnel, the patient- and family-centered active holistic care of patients with advanced, progressive disease. Essential components of palliative care are: pain and symptom control, communication regarding treatment and alternatives, prognosis, and available services, rehabilitation services, care that addresses treatment and palliative concerns, intellectual, emotional, social, and spiritual needs, terminal care, support in bereavement. The goal of palliative care is an achievement of the best quality of life for patients and their families.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Patient Hospice Care Referral Yes No Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no indicator for information related to a patient referral to hospice care.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Patient Hospice Care Referral Date
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The date for information related to a patient referral to hospice care.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Patient Palliative Therapy Referral Reason
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The reason for a patient referral to palliative care, the patient- and family-centered active holistic care of patients with advanced, progressive disease. Essential components of palliative care are: pain and symptom control, communication regarding treatment and alternatives, prognosis, and available services, rehabilitation services, care that addresses treatment and palliative concerns, intellectual, emotional, social, and spiritual needs, terminal care, support in bereavement. The goal of palliative care is an achievement of the best quality of life for patients and their families.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Patient Palliative Therapy Referral Other Specify Text
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The free text field related to a patient referral to palliative care, the patient- and family-centered active holistic care of patients with advanced, progressive disease. Essential components of palliative care are: pain and symptom control, communication regarding treatment and alternatives, prognosis, and available services, rehabilitation services, care that addresses treatment and palliative concerns, intellectual, emotional, social, and spiritual needs, terminal care, support in bereavement. The goal of palliative care is an achievement of the best quality of life for patients and their families.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Patient Palliative Therapy Personnel Assessment First Date
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The first date of a patient's assessment by palliative care personnel, the patient- and family-centered active holistic care of patients with advanced, progressive disease. Essential components of palliative care are: pain and symptom control, communication regarding treatment and alternatives, prognosis, and available services, rehabilitation services, care that addresses treatment and palliative concerns, intellectual, emotional, social, and spiritual needs, terminal care, support in bereavement. The goal of palliative care is an achievement of the best quality of life for patients and their families.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Patient Hospice Care Enrollment Yes No Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no indicator for information related to a patient's enrollment in hospice care.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Patient Hospice Care Enrollment Date
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The date related to a patient's enrollment in hospice care.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Patient Hospice Care Discontinue Yes No Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no indicator for information related to the discontinuation of hospice care by a patient.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Patient Hospice Care Discontinue Reason Text
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The free text field that describes the reason of the discontinuation of hospice care by a patient.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Patient Palliative Therapy Personnel Assessment Date
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The date related to a patient's assessment by palliative care personnel, the patient- and family-centered active holistic care of patients with advanced, progressive disease. Essential components of palliative care are: pain and symptom control, communication regarding treatment and alternatives, prognosis, and available services, rehabilitation services, care that addresses treatment and palliative concerns, intellectual, emotional, social, and spiritual needs, terminal care, support in bereavement. The goal of palliative care is an achievement of the best quality of life for patients and their families.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Patient Palliative Therapy Personnel Assessment Setting Type
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The patient setting type related to a patient's assessment by palliative care personnel, the patient- and family-centered active holistic care of patients with advanced, progressive disease. Essential components of palliative care are: pain and symptom control, communication regarding treatment and alternatives, prognosis, and available services, rehabilitation services, care that addresses treatment and palliative concerns, intellectual, emotional, social, and spiritual needs, terminal care, support in bereavement. The goal of palliative care is an achievement of the best quality of life for patients and their families.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Patient Emergency Care Evaluation Date
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The date related to an evaluation of a patient in the ER (emergency care).

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Patient Emergency Care Evaluation Reason Text
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The reason related to an evaluation of a patient in the ER (emergency care).

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Hospital Discharge Code Status
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The code status for a hospital discharge.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Hospital Intensive Care Unit Admission Reason Text
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The reason related to an admission into an intensive care unit (a health care facility unit that provides intensive care to critically ill patients and patients with complex medical problems who require constant monitoring or special therapy) of a hospital.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Caregiver Withdraw Consent Date
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The date related to a caregiver (the primary person in charge of the care of a patient) withdrawing consent on a trial.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Diagnostic Procedure Assessment Data Source
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The data source of the assessment for a diagnostic procedure.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: QRS COMPLEX Finding Time in Millisecond Number
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The measurement and evaluation of the QRS complex electrical activity on an electrocardiogram, expressed in milliseconds.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Electrocardiogram Change From Previous Assessment Clinically Significant Status
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The status related to the clinical significance of a change in the comparison of an ECG to the previous assessment.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Electrocardiogram Change From Previous Assessment Text
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The free text field to specific information related to change in the comparison of an ECG to the previous assessment.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Diagnostic Electrocardiogram Prior Performed Date
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The date related to a prior diagnostic electrocardiogram (ECG), measurement and interpretation of electrical manifestations of heart activity, being performed.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Patient Reported Outcome Oral Symptoms Rinse Use Pain Relief Assessment Yes No Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no indicator for information on the Patient Completed Oral Symptoms assessment regarding use of the oral rinse (specifically related to pain relief), collected directly from a patient that typically includes subjective feelings regarding symptoms, functions in daily life, physical, mental, emotional, spiritual, and social well being, and satisfaction with his/her health care.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Patient Reported Outcome Oral Symptoms Rinse Use Negation Effective Assessment Yes No Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no indicator for information on the Patient Completed Oral Symptoms assessment regarding use of the oral rinse (specifically related to study rinse being ineffective), collected directly from a patient that typically includes subjective feelings regarding symptoms, functions in daily life, physical, mental, emotional, spiritual, and social well being, and satisfaction with his/her health care.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Patient Reported Outcome Oral Symptoms Rinse Use Side Effect Assessment Yes No Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no indicator for information on the Patient Completed Oral Symptoms assessment regarding use of the oral rinse (specifically related to side effects of the study rinse), collected directly from a patient that typically includes subjective feelings regarding symptoms, functions in daily life, physical, mental, emotional, spiritual, and social well being, and satisfaction with his/her health care.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Patient Reported Outcome Oral Symptoms Rinse Use Other Assessment Yes No Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no indicator for information on the Patient Completed Oral Symptoms assessment regarding other use of the oral rinse, collected directly from a patient that typically includes subjective feelings regarding symptoms, functions in daily life, physical, mental, emotional, spiritual, and social well being, and satisfaction with his/her health care.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Prior Therapy Administered Count
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The count related to the number of lines of prior therapy administered.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Anthracycline Therapy Administration Yes No Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no indicator for information relating to the administration of an anthracycline (a member of a family of anticancer drugs that are also antibiotics) treatment regimen.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Therapeutic Procedure Trabectedin Administered Yes No Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no indicator related to the administration of trabectedin, a tetrahydroisoquinoline alkaloid isolated from the marine tunicate Ecteinascidia turbinata with potential antineoplastic activity. Binding to the minor groove of DNA, trabectedin interferes with the transcription-coupled nucleotide excision repair machinery to induce lethal DNA strand breaks and blocks the cell cycle in the G2 phase.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Therapeutic Procedure Taxane Compound Administered Yes No Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no indicator for information related to the administration of a taxane compound therapy, a type of drug that blocks cell growth by stopping mitosis (cell division). Taxanes interfere with microtubules (cellular structures that help move chromosomes during mitosis).

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Therapeutic Procedure Gemcitabine Administered Yes No Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no indicator for information related to the administration of gemcitabine, a type of antimetabolite.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Therapeutic Procedure Platinum-Based Administered Yes No Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no indicator for information related to the administration of a platinum-based therapy.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Therapeutic Procedure Targeted Therapy Administered Yes No Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no indicator for information related to the administration of targeted therapy, therapeutic agents to produce an effect that is intended to alter or stop a pathologic process. A type of treatment that uses drugs or other substances, such as monoclonal antibodies, to identify and attack specific cancer cells. Targeted therapy may have fewer side effects than other types of cancer treatments.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Hepatic Metastasis Diagnosis Yes No Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no indicator related to liver cancer that has spread from the organ in which it first appeared to another organ being diagnosed.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Nitrosourea Compound Administered End Date
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The end date for treatment with nitrosourea, a group of anticancer drugs that can cross the blood-brain barrier.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Person Prior Therapy Toxicity Personal Medical History Yes No Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no indicator for information related to a personal medical history of toxicity after administration of a therapeutic procedure/therapy.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Person Pericardial Effusion Personal Medical History Yes No Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no indicator of information related to a personal medical history of pericardial effusion, fluid collection within the pericardial sac, usually due to inflammation.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Person Pericardial Effusion Personal Medical History End Date
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The date on which an observation or an ended related to a personal medical history of pericardial effusion, fluid collection within the pericardial sac, usually due to inflammation.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Person Pleural Effusion Personal Medical History Yes No Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no indicator for information related to a personal medical history of pleural effusion, increased amounts of fluid within the pleural cavity. Symptoms include shortness of breath, cough, and chest pain. It is usually caused by lung infections, congestive heart failure, pleural and lung tumors, connective tissue disorders, and trauma.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Person Pleural Effusion Personal Medical History End Date
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The date on which an observation or an ended related to a personal medical history of pleural effusion, increased amounts of fluid within the pleural cavity. Symptoms include shortness of breath, cough, and chest pain. It is usually caused by lung infections, congestive heart failure, pleural and lung tumors, connective tissue disorders, and trauma.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Prior Therapeutic Procedure Trabectedin Administered Yes No Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no indicator for information related to the prior administration of trabectedin, a tetrahydroisoquinoline alkaloid isolated from the marine tunicate Ecteinascidia turbinata with potential antineoplastic activity. Binding to the minor groove of DNA, trabectedin interferes with the transcription-coupled nucleotide excision repair machinery to induce lethal DNA strand breaks and blocks the cell cycle in the G2 phase.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Medication Thyroid Gland Supplement Administered Yes No Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no indicator related to the administration of a medication for thyroid supplementation The thyroid, an endocrine gland located at the base of the neck produces and secretes thyroxine and other hormones. Thyroxine is important for metabolic control.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Malignant Neoplasm Glioma Histologic Grade Type
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The type related to the assessment of histologic grade in a glioma, a benign or malignant brain and spinal cord tumor that arises from glial cells (astrocytes, oligodendrocytes, ependymal cells).

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Informed Consent Form Investigator Signed Date
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The date related to the informed consent form, a patient's signed consent to participate in various research activities, being signed by the site investigator.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Specimen ICF Investigator Signed Date
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The date related to specimen informed consent formed signed by the site investigator.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Personal Medical History Anxiety Depression Disease or Disorder Yes No Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no indicator for information related to a person's medical history of anxiety or depression.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Personal Medical History Other Mental Health Disease or Disorder Yes No Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no indicator for information related to a person's medical history of other mental health disorders.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Personal Medical History Other Mental Health Disease or Disorder Specify
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The free text field for information related to a person's medical history of other mental health disorders.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Medication Anxiety Depression Use Yes No Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no indicator for information related to the use of medications for the treatment of anxiety and/or depression.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Medication Other Mental Health Disease or Disorder Use Yes No Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no indicator for information related to the use of medications for the treatment of other mental health disorders.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Malignant Neoplasm Other Nodal Involvement Yes No Unknown Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no/unknown indicator for information related to the involvement of a malignant neoplasm involved with or pertaining to a node, any bulge or swelling of an anatomical structure or part, other than those previously mentioned.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Malignant Neoplasm Other Nodal Involvement Specify
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The free text field to specify information related to the involvement of a malignant neoplasm involved with or pertaining to a node, any bulge or swelling of an anatomical structure or part, other than those previously mentioned.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Tumor Histologic Classification Type
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The type related to tumor histologic classification.
DataElementQueryResults.administrativeNotes: 1/19/2023: added AQT per CADSR0001933.wz

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Malignant Testicular Germ Cell Tumor International Germ Cell Consensus Classification Prognosis Yes No Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no indicator related to International Germ Cell Cancer Collaborative Group (IGCCG) staging being performed.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Laboratory Procedure Human Chorionic Gonadotropin Outcome Value
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The numerical laboratory value related to the outcome of the laboratory procedure on human chorionic gonadotropin (HCG), a sialoglycoprotein hormone secreted by the placenta and maintains the corpus luteum at the beginning of the gestation period.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Person International Prognostic Factor Study Group Metastatic Germ Cell Tumor Assessment Modified Risk Category
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The modified risk category related to an assessment of International Prognostic Factors Study Group (IPFSG) risk classification for persons with metastatic germ cell tumors.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Participant Enrollment Region Name
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The name of the region related to participant enrollment.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Laboratory Procedure Elevation Prior Value Assessment Yes No Not Applicable Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no/not applicable indicator for information related to the rise of a laboratory value from the prior assessment.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Prior Specimen Collection Occurrence Date
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The date related to the occurrence of a prior specimen collection.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Prior Laboratory Procedure Outcome Value
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The value related to the outcome of a prior laboratory procedure.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Disease or Disorder Growing Teratoma Syndrome Present Yes No Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no indicator for information related to the presence of growing teratoma syndrome (GTS), a condition characterized by the presence of a growing mature teratoma in a patient during or after chemotherapy for a non-seminomatous germ cell tumor, with normal serum markers for human chorionic gonadotropin and alpha fetoprotein. Complete surgical resection is the preferred treatment.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Malignant Neoplasm Teratoma Pathology Confirmation Assessment Yes No Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no indicator for information related to an assessment of a pathologically confirmed teratoma, a non-seminomatous germ cell tumor characterized by the presence of various tissues which correspond to the different germinal layers (endoderm, mesoderm, and ectoderm). It occurs in the testis, ovary, and extragonadal sites including central nervous system, mediastinum, lung, and stomach.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Procedure Leukapheresis Performed Yes No Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no indicator for information related to leukapheresis (removal of the blood to collect specific blood cells; the remaining blood is returned to the body) being performed.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Peripheral Blood Stem Cell CD34+ Cell Harvest Performed Day Count
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The number of days related to a peripheral blood stem CD34+ cell harvest performed.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Laboratory Procedure Lactate Dehydrogenase Result Yes No Unknown Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no/unknown indicator for information related to the result of the medical procedure that involves testing a sample of blood for lactic dehydrogenase, a family of homotetrameric cytoplasmic enzymes involved in the conversion of L-lactate and NAD to pyruvate and NADH in the final step of anaerobic glycolysis.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Laboratory Procedure Human Chorionic Gonadotropin Outcome Yes No Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no indicator for information related to the outcome of the laboratory procedure on human chorionic gonadotropin (HCG), a sialoglycoprotein hormone secreted by the placenta and maintains the corpus luteum at the beginning of the gestation period.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Surgical Excision Residual Lesion Performed Yes No Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no indicator for information related to the surgical resection of residual lesions.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Increased Tumor Size Present Percentage Value
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The percentage related to an increase in tumor size.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Malignant Neoplasm Residual Mass Pathology Assessment Type
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The type related to the pathology of residual masses.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Malignant Neoplasm Germ Cell Tumor Follow-up Assessment Status
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The status related to the follow-up assessment of a germ cell tumor.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Participant Germany Study Site Enrollment Yes No Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no indicator for information related to participant study site enrollment occurring in Germany.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Malignant Neoplasm Lesion Cross Boundary Assessment Yes No Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no indicator for information related to a malignant neoplasm lesion crossing the boundaries of multiple anatomic sites.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Bone Involved Lesion Type
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The type of bone lesion involvement.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Bone Scan Tracer Axial Skeleton Uptake Yes No Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no indicator for information related to tracer uptake in the axial skeleton, the part of the skeleton that includes the skull and spinal column and sternum and ribs.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Bone Scan Tracer Appendicular Skeleton Uptake Yes No Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no indicator for information related to tracer uptake in the appendicular skeleton, the part of the skeleton that includes the bones of the upper and lower limbs.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Bone Scan Tracer New Anatomic Site Uptake Yes No Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no indicator for information related to tracer uptake in a new anatomic site.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Neoadjuvant Endocrine Therapy Administered First Date
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The first administration date related to neoadjuvant (treatment given as a first step to shrink a tumor before the main treatment) endocrine therapy, which is/are various treatment modalities that produce the desired therapeutic effect by means of change of hormone/hormones level. The treatment may include administration of hormones or hormone analogs to the patient, or decreasing the level of hormones in the body by using hormone antagonists, or hormone ablation therapy.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Neoadjuvant Endocrine Therapy Administered Yes No Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no indicator for information related to the administration of neoadjuvant (treatment given as a first step to shrink a tumor before the main treatment) endocrine therapy, which is/are various treatment modalities that produce the desired therapeutic effect by means of change of hormone/hormones level. The treatment may include administration of hormones or hormone analogs to the patient, or decreasing the level of hormones in the body by using hormone antagonists, or hormone ablation therapy.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Prior Adjuvant Chemotherapy Administered Count
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The quantity of regimens related receiving earlier in time agents given to augment or stimulate a primary therapy administered for disease.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Adjuvant Therapy Discontinued Early Administered Yes No Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no indicator for information related to the early discontinuation of adjuvant therapy.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Endocrine Therapy Administered Yes No Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no indicator for information related to the administration of endocrine therapy, which is/are various treatment modalities that produce the desired therapeutic effect by means of change of hormone/hormones level. The treatment may include administration of hormones or hormone analogs to the patient, or decreasing the level of hormones in the body by using hormone antagonists, or hormone ablation therapy.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Prior Neoadjuvant Endocrine Therapy Administered Yes No Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no indicator for information related to the prior administration of neoadjuvant (treatment given as a first step to shrink a tumor before the main treatment) endocrine therapy, which is/are various treatment modalities that produce the desired therapeutic effect by means of change of hormone/hormones level. The treatment may include administration of hormones or hormone analogs to the patient, or decreasing the level of hormones in the body by using hormone antagonists, or hormone ablation therapy.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Systemic Therapy Discontinued Early Administered Yes No Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no indicator for information related to the early discontinuation of systemic therapy.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Prior Systemic Endocrine Therapy Administered Yes No Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no indicator for information related to the prior administration of systemic endocrine therapy, which is/are various treatment modalities that produce the desired therapeutic effect by means of change of hormone/hormones level. The treatment may include administration of hormones or hormone analogs to the patient, or decreasing the level of hormones in the body by using hormone antagonists, or hormone ablation therapy.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Neoplasm Soft Tissue Sarcoma Diagnosis Subtype
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The subtype related to the scientific determination and investigation, analysis and recognition of the presence and nature of disease, condition, or injury from expressed signs and symptoms of tissue growth resulting from uncontrolled cell proliferation.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Neoplasm Soft Tissue Sarcoma Diagnosis Specify
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The free-text field related to the scientific determination and investigation, analysis and recognition of the presence and nature of disease, condition, or injury from expressed signs and symptoms of tissue growth resulting from uncontrolled cell proliferation.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Non-Protocol Therapy Pazopanib Administered Yes No Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no indicator for information related to the administration of pazopanib in a non-protocol setting.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Patient Endocrine Therapy Resistance Process Status
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The status related to a patient's endocrine therapy resistance process, activities of biologic molecules or complexes involved in processes that maintain immunity to, or counteract, defeat, or withstand the effects of, an antagonistic agent.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Prior Therapeutic Procedure Fulvestrant Everolimus Administered Stratification Type
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The stratification factor related to the prior administration of fulvestrant and/or everolimus.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Prior Monoclonal Antibody Administered Last Date
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The date of last administration for the prior use of an antibody produced by a clone or genetically homogenous fast-growing cells, i.e., hybridoma. Hybridoma cells are cloned to establish cell lines producing a specific antibody that is chemically and immunologically homogeneous and are widely used in cancer detection, diagnosis, and treatment.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Primary Left Breast Tumor Laterality Yes No Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no indicator for information related to primary tumor being located in the left breast.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Primary Right Breast Tumor Laterality Yes No Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no indicator for information related to primary tumor being located in the right breast.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Other Prior Neoadjuvant Endocrine Therapy Administered Yes No Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no indicator for information related to the prior administration of neoadjuvant (treatment given as a first step to shrink a tumor before the main treatment) endocrine therapy, other than those previously mentioned, which is/are various treatment modalities that produce the desired therapeutic effect by means of change of hormone/hormones level. The treatment may include administration of hormones or hormone analogs to the patient, or decreasing the level of hormones in the body by using hormone antagonists, or hormone ablation therapy.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Other Prior Adjuvant Endocrine Therapy Administered Yes No Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no indicator for information related to other prior adjuvant endocrine therapy being administered.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Prior Therapeutic Procedure Palbociclib Everolimus Administered Stratification Type
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The stratification type related to the prior administration of palbociclib and/or everolimus.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Patient Correlative Study Sufficient Tissue Assessment Yes No Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no indicator for information related to an assessment to determine if tissue is sufficient for a correlative study.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Sum Nodal Lesion Absolute Increase Diameter Yes No Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no indicator for information related to an absolute increase of the post-baseline sum of the dimensions (PBSD) (sum of the longest diameter for all target lesions plus the sum of the short axis of all the target lymph nodes) from the minimum sum of the dimensions (MSD).

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Malignant Neoplasm Breast Carcinoma Focus Assessment Count
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The quantity related to the assessment of the number of foci in breast carcinoma.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Laboratory Procedure Thyroid Stimulating Hormone Thyrotropin Measurement Date
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The date relating to the result of the medical procedure that involves testing a sample of blood for thyroid stimulating hormone (TSH), a hormone produced by the pituitary gland that stimulates the release of thyroid hormone from thyroglobulin.
DataElementQueryResults.administrativeNotes: 1/31/2023: added AQT per CADSR0001988.wz

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Prior Systemic Therapy Administered Count
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: A numerical quantity related to the prior systemic therapy administered.
DataElementQueryResults.administrativeNotes: 2023/4/4: Added AQT for Alliance.wz

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Prophylactic Antibiotic Administered Yes No Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no indicator for the administration of prophylactic (something that prevents or protects) antibiotics, a substance that kills microorganisms such as bacteria or mold, or stops them from growing and causing disease.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Positron Emission Tomography Diagnostic Imaging Malignant Neoplasm Disease Response Assessment Yes No Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no indicator related to a disease response assessment by FDG PET imaging.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Clinical Study Carcinoma T Stage Stratification Type
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The type related to the stratification of patients via T stage, T refers to the extent of tumor involvement at the primary site.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Endoscopic Procedure Performed Yes No Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no indicator for information related to a procedure that uses an endoscope to examine the inside of the body. An endoscope is a thin, tube-like instrument with a light and a lens for viewing. It may also have a tool to remove tissue to be checked under a microscope for signs of disease.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Diagnostic Imaging Endoscopic Ultrasound Performed Yes No Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no indicator for information relating to endoscopic ultrasound, an ultrasound administered by using a tube containing flexible fiber optic wires that allows for the analysis of tissues inside the body, being performed as a method of diagnostic evaluation.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Disease Progression Suspicion Assessment Yes No Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no indicator for information related to an assessment of the suspicion of progression disease, which is the worsening of a disease over time.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Diagnostic Imaging Barium Esophagram Performed Yes No Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no indicator for information related to a barium esophagram being performed, a series of x-ray pictures of the esophagus taken after a patient drinks a liquid containing barium sulfate (a form of the silver-white metallic element barium). The barium sulfate coats and outlines the inner wall of the esophagus so that it can be seen on the x-ray pictures.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Gastrointestinal Surgical Procedure Performed Type
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The type related to a gastrointestinal surgical procedure being performed.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Gastrointestinal Surgical Procedure Performed Specify
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The free text field for information related to a gastrointestinal surgical procedure being performed.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Gastric Carcinoma Histologic Type
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Information related to the histologic type of a gastric carcinoma.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: External Beam Radiation Therapy Administered Begin Date
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The start date related to the administered external beam radiation therapy.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: External Beam Radiation Therapy Administered End Date
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The end date for information related to the administered external beam radiation therapy.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Therapeutic Procedure Ramucirumab Administered Yes No Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no indicator for information related to the administration of ramucirumab, a recombinant, fully human monoclonal antibody directed against human vascular endothelial growth factor receptor 2 (VEGFR-2) with antiangiogenesis activity. Ramucirumab specifically binds to and inhibits VEGFR-2, which may result in an inhibition of tumor angiogenesis and a decrease in tumor nutrient supply. VEGFR-2 is a pro-angiogenic growth factor receptor tyrosine kinase expressed by endothelial cells.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Therapeutic Procedure Irinotecan Administered Yes No Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no indicator for information related to the administration of irinotecan, a semisynthetic derivative of camptothecin, a cytotoxic, quinoline-based alkaloid extracted from the Asian tree Camptotheca acuminata.  Irinotecan, a prodrug, is converted to a biologically active metabolite 7-ethyl-10-hydroxy-camptothecin (SN-38) by a carboxylesterase-converting enzyme.  One thousand-fold more potent than its parent compound irinotecan, SN-38 inhibits topoisomerase I activity by stabilizing the cleavable complex between topoisomerase I and DNA, resulting in DNA breaks that inhibit DNA replication and trigger apoptotic cell death.  Because ongoing DNA synthesis is necessary for irinotecan to exert its cytotoxic effects, it is classified as an S-phase-specific agent.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Transplant Conditioning Regimen Type
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The type of treatment regimen related to preparing a person for receipt of a transplant.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Standard Uptake Value Positron Emission Tomography Reduction Assessment Percentage Value
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The percentage relating to an assessment of the reduction in standard uptake value during positron emission tomography.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Central Pathology Review Outcome Date
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The date related to the result by a centralized laboratory.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Meningioma Present Yes No Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no indicator for information related to the presence of a generally slow growing tumor attached to the dura mater. It is composed of neoplastic meningothelial (arachnoidal) cells. It typically occurs in adults, often women and it has a wide range of histopathological appearances. Of the various subtypes, meningothelial, fibrous and transitional meningiomas are the most common. Most meningiomas are WHO grade I tumors, and some are WHO grade II or III tumors. Most subtypes share a common clinical behavior, although some subtypes are more likely to recur and follow a more aggressive clinical course. (Adapted from WHO)

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Gene Mutation Detection Detection Type
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The type related to the gene mutation detected.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Local Pathologic Diagnosis Meningioma Assessment Yes No Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no indicator for information related to the local pathologic diagnosis of meningioma.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Brain Tumor Histopathologic Grade Type
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The type for information related to histologic grade or measure of differentiation of a brain tumor.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Surgical Procedure Craniotomy Performed Yes No Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no indicator for information related to a craniotomy being performed.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Surgical Procedure Craniotomy Performed Date
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The date for information related to a craniotomy being performed.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Laboratory Procedure Total Testosterone Outcome Specified Value
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The specific value related to the determination of the amount of free and bound testosterone present in a sample.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Diagnostic Imaging Other Diseases and Disorders Research Consent Yes No Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no indicator for information related to consent for the use of diagnostic images for use in future research to learn about, prevent or treat other health problems

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Patient Controlled Thyroid Gland Function Clinical Trial Eligibility Criteria Yes No Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no indicator for eligibility criteria related to controlled thyroid gland function.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Brief Fatigue Inventory Worst Fatigue Assessment Score
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The score pertaining to the worst fatigue score on the 9-item questionnaire, developed by Cleeland and Mendoza, designed to assess the severity of fatigue and the impact of fatigue on daily functioning in cancer patients.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Disease or Disorder Solitary Plasmacytoma Risk Assessment Category
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The category used to describe risk assessment of a subject with solitary plasmacytoma.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Laboratory Procedure Serum M Protein Outcome Date
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The date related to the results of the medical procedure that involves testing a sample of blood serum, the clear liquid part of the blood that remains after blood cells and clotting proteins have been removed, for monoclonal immunoglobulin, a protein complex comprised of two heavy chains and two light chains that is found in abundance in patients who have multiple myeloma; the protein is not produced in response to an antigen, but it is expressed in malignant plasma cells and excreted into the blood and urine.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Laboratory Procedure Urine M Protein Outcome Date
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The date related to the result of the medical procedure that involves testing a sample of urine, the fluid that is excreted by the kidneys for a protein complex comprised of two heavy chains and two light chains.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Surgical Procedure Diagnostic Biopsy Performed Date
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The date related to the removal and pathologic examination of specimens for diagnostic purposes.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Surgical Procedure Plasmacytoma Biopsy Performed Yes No Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no indicator for information related to a biopsy of a plasmacytoma being performed.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Serum M Protein Laboratory Procedure Performed Yes No Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no indicator for information related to a serum M-protein laboratory procedure being performed.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Disease or Disorder Radiation-Induced Dermatitis Present Yes No Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no indicator for information related to a cutaneous inflammatory reaction occurring as a result of exposure to biologically effective levels of ionizing radiation.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Malignant Neoplasm Bone Assessment Yes No Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no indicator for information related to the assessment of a malignant neoplasm of the bone.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Disease Osteoporosis Diagnosis WHO Criteria Category
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: Category of the WHO Criteria for diagnosis of osteoporosis, a loss of bone mass and strength due to nutritional, metabolic, or other factors, usually resulting in deformity or fracture, that causes discomfort, dysfunction, or distress to the person affected or those in contact with the person.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Minimal Residual Disease Assessment Yes No Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no indicator for information related to the assessment of the remainder of a tumor or a neoplasm/cancer after primary, potentially curative therapy.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no/not applicable indicator for information related to a diagnostic assessment of avidity (strength of binding, usually of a small molecule with multiple binding sites by a larger, particularly the binding of a complex antigen by an antibody) of a Positron Emission Tomography, a computerized image of the metabolic activity of body tissues used to determine the presence of disease.

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Cytogenetic Abnormality Trisomy Chromosome 3 Present Yes No Unk ND NA Indicator

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Cytogenetic Abnormality Trisomy Chromosome 7 Present Yes No Unk ND NA Indicator

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Cytogenetic Abnormality Trisomy Chromosome 15 Present Yes No Unk ND NA Indicator

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Specimen Hyperdiploidy Cytogenetic Abnormality Present Yes No Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no indicator for information related to the presence of the cytogenetic abnormality, hyperdiploidy (a chromosomal abnormality in which the chromosomal number is greater than the normal diploid number).

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Cytogenetic Abnormality 1q Present Yes No Indicator

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Laboratory Procedure Immunoglobulin Light Chain Kappa Immunoglobulin Light Chain Lambda Result Value
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The value for information relating to a medical procedure that involves testing of dissolved proteins of blood plasma for Kappa immunoglobulin light chain, one of the light chains of the immunoglobulins with a molecular weight of approximately 22 kD, and for Lambda Immunoglobulin Light Chain, one of two Ig light chain types (each Ig molecule is typically composed of two heavy chains and two light chains but Ig lambda light chains contain a variable and a constant region).

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Laboratory Procedure Immunoglobulin Light Chain Kappa Immunoglobulin Light Chain Lambda Result Date
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The date for information relating to a medical procedure that involves testing of dissolved proteins of blood plasma for Kappa immunoglobulin light chain, one of the light chains of the immunoglobulins with a molecular weight of approximately 22 kD, and for Lambda Immunoglobulin Light Chain, one of two Ig light chain types (each Ig molecule is typically composed of two heavy chains and two light chains but Ig lambda light chains contain a variable and a constant region).

DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no indicator for information related to a breast conservation surgical procedure being performed.  Breast conservation treatment is defined as excision of the primary tumor and adjacent breast tissue, followed by radiation therapy.  This procedure is also referred to as lumpectomy, segmental mastectomy, or partial mastectomy. (from Consensus Statements: Treatment of Early-stage Breast Cancer, 1990)

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Daratumumab Administered Indicator
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The yes/no indicator related to the act of having given a fully human monoclonal antibody directed against the cell surface glycoprotein CD-38 with potential antineoplastic activity. The binding of anti-CD38 monoclonal antibody to natural killer (NK) cells mimics the normal CD38-CD31 interaction on the NK cell surface. CD38 is also present on multiple myeloma (MM) cells and plasma leukemia cells; this agent may preferentially bind these cells, triggering antitumoral antibody-dependent cellular cytotoxicity (ADCC) and complement-dependent cytotoxicity (CDC). CD38, a cell surface glycoprotein, is present on various immune cells and has been shown to regulate the cytotoxic response of activated NK cells.
DataElementQueryResults.changeNote: 12/1/2017: CM Released as part of draft content review

DataElementQueryResults.preferredName: Importance Weight Treatment 6 Mercaptopurine Pill Importance Weight Type
DataElementQueryResults.preferredDefinition: The relative importance granted to something._An action or administration of therapeutic agents to produce an effect that is intended to alter the course of a pathologic process._A natural number greater than 5 and less than 7 and the quantity that it denotes: the sum of five and one._A thiopurine-derivative antimetabolite with antineoplastic and immunosuppressive activities.  Produced through the metabolism of mercaptopurine by hypoxanthine-guanine phosphoribosyltransferase (HGPRT), mercaptopurine metabolites 6-thioguanosine-5'-phosphate (6-thioGMP) and 6-thioinosine monophosphate (T-IMP) inhibit nucleotide interconversions and de novo purine synthesis, thereby blocking the formation of purine nucleotides and inhibiting DNA synthesis.  This agent is also incorporated into DNA in the form of deoxythioguanosine, which results in the disruption of DNA replication. In addition, mercaptopurine is converted to 6-methylmercaptopurine ribonucleoside (MMPR) by 6-thiopurine methyltransferase; MMPRs are also potent inhibitors of de novo purine synthesis. (NCI04)_A solid composed of a small, round object composed of active and/or inert ingredient(s)._The text that describes the relative importance of a factor.
